This chapter really resonated with me. I felt like this was a pretty good explanation of our family. Of any family. Recognizing the dysfunctional past
we shared.
I thought we were on the same page, making hard won progress. I wish I knew you felt differently so I could have tried to do even more. I just didn’t.
When this all happened, you were my world. I would have done anything humanly possible for you. I tried to show you every day- lunches, dates,
walks, sex.
I honestly believed what I was seeing.
